fonts.description:
Google Fonts configuration. Two formats supported:

  Option A — full URL: { "url": "https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Playfair+Display:wght@400;700&family=Inter:wght@400;500;600&display=swap" }

  Option B — family list: { "families": ["Playfair Display:wght@400;700", "Inter:wght@400;500;600"] }

The families are injected as a <link> tag in the page <head>.

propOverrides.description:
Map of displayName → style patches. Each value can have { root, mobile, desktop } keys with Tailwind class objects.

Example:
  {"Section": {"root": {"background": "bg-(--primary)"}, "mobile": {"py": "py-20"}, "desktop": {"py": "py-32"}}}

nodes.description:
Flat CraftJS node map: { nodeId: nodeDefinition, ... }. Each node definition must include:

  {
    "type": { "resolvedName": "Container" },  // Component type
    "isCanvas": true,                          // true if it can have children
    "props": {
      "canDelete": true,
      "canEditName": true,
      "type": "section",                       // "section" for root, omit for children
      "root": { "background": "bg-(--primary)" },
      "mobile": { "display": "flex", "flexDirection": "flex-col", "width": "w-full", "py": "py-12", "px": "px-6" },
      "desktop": { "py": "py-20", "px": "px-16" },
      "custom": { "displayName": "My Block" }
    },
    "parent": "page_home",                     // parent node ID
    "nodes": ["child_id_1", "child_id_2"],     // ordered child IDs
    "linkedNodes": {}
  }

Available component types: Container, Text, Image, Button, ButtonList, ImageList, Form, FormElement, Divider, Spacer, Video, Audio, Embed.
Use get_component_schema for full prop details.

description:
Surgically patches a single node on the active site (GET → patch → PUT). Same as patch_site_node but with image URL validation.

Patches are shallow-merged into the target object. Use unset* arrays to remove keys that merges cannot delete.

Common uses:
  - Change text: propsPatch: { "text": "New heading" }
  - Change colors: rootPatch: { "background": "bg-(--accent)", "color": "text-(--accent-foreground)" }
  - Change mobile layout: mobilePatch: { "flexDirection": "flex-col", "py": "py-8" }
  - Change desktop layout: propsPatch: { "desktop": { "gridCols": "grid-cols-3" } }
  - Reorder children: nodesPatch: ["child2", "child1", "child3"]
  - Remove a prop: unsetMobile: ["gap"] removes gap from mobile styles

node.description:
Node definition. Must include:
  type: { resolvedName: "Text" | "Container" | "Image" | "Button" | "ButtonList" | etc }
  isCanvas: true (containers) or false (leaf elements)
  props: { canDelete: true, canEditName: true, root: {}, mobile: {}, desktop: {}, text/content/etc, custom: { displayName: "..." } }

parent and linkedNodes are set automatically — do not include them.
